name: epic
version: 1.0.0
description: "Grand narrative chronicle style"
author: "commitlore"
llm_prompt: |
  Write the changelog as an epic narrative chronicle, as if recounting
  the legendary deeds of heroes in a fantasy saga. Every commit is a
  quest fulfilled. Every bug fix is a dragon slain. Use grandiose,
  archaic language. Address the reader as if reading from an ancient
  scroll. End with a prophetic teaser of what is to come.
templates:
  header: "📜 THE CHRONICLES OF THIS REPOSITORY"
  feature: "  And so it came to pass — {{.Author}} forged: {{.Message}}"
  fix: "  The ancient bug was vanquished by {{.Author}}: {{.Message}}"
  breaking: "  ⚡ The old ways were shattered: {{.Message}}"
  footer: "Thus ends another chapter in the saga."
